WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.789
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.290 --> 00:14.320
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.340 --> 00:19.065
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:19.085 --> 00:20.246
Good morning and welcome.

00:20.286 --> 00:21.888
I'm so glad that you're here today.

00:21.908 --> 00:27.954
I want to welcome those of you at our West Campus and those of you who are joining us

00:28.258 --> 00:32.064
either on Facebook Live or on our webcast or on television.

00:32.084 --> 00:35.309
We're so thankful that you are here with us today.

00:35.369 --> 00:42.059
Let's open our Bibles this morning to Matthew chapter 24 verse 45.

00:42.499 --> 00:57.682
We have been in a series of messages called Storm Warning about Matthew 24 and 25, commonly referred to biblically as the Olivet Discourse where Jesus talked about the end times.

00:58.114 --> 01:05.563
And this morning, we're going to just continue that with a couple of parables that Jesus told that are very, very instructive for us.

01:06.304 --> 01:16.997
I don't know why it is, but have you ever noticed that the only time that batteries run down in a smoke detector is at about 2 a.m.

01:18.018 --> 01:23.085
They never start beeping at about 8.30 in the morning or about 2.30 in the afternoon.

01:23.505 --> 01:27.410
It's 2.30 a.m. when in the middle of the night you hear that

01:27.490 --> 01:27.971
Chirp.

01:29.993 --> 01:30.855
Maybe it was just once.

01:31.556 --> 01:31.916
Chirp.

01:33.618 --> 01:34.419
Maybe it'll go away.

01:34.660 --> 01:35.060
Chirp.

01:36.062 --> 01:37.644
And you have to get up in the middle of the night.

01:38.265 --> 01:47.898
And for us, where ours are positioned, drag out a ladder, change the battery in the smoke detector in order just to go back to sleep.

01:48.839 --> 01:56.690
However, according to the National Fire Protection Association, 72%

01:56.802 --> 02:02.349
of all fire fatalities are due to no working smoke detector.

02:03.090 --> 02:08.136
It's not a lack of information that causes those fatalities.

02:08.336 --> 02:09.998
It's a lack of preparation.

02:11.780 --> 02:19.009
This morning, we're going to talk about how to be prepared for the coming of the Lord.

02:19.990 --> 02:26.258
You see, the leading obstacle to preparation is always procrastination.

02:27.010 --> 02:31.975
We put off until tomorrow what we should be doing today.

02:32.856 --> 02:50.813
We put off until some point in the future when we're pressured to do something, what we could do in a more relaxed and leisurely fashion, what we could do in a much more life-giving fashion rather than cramming things together.

02:51.554 --> 02:55.538
My favorite quote about procrastination, to prevent procrastination,

02:56.034 --> 02:57.015
is anonymous.

02:57.035 --> 02:57.977
So I don't know who said it.

02:58.798 --> 03:04.326
But the cost of procrastination is the life you could have lived.

03:05.448 --> 03:07.631
I've always liked that quote.

03:07.651 --> 03:15.122
You see, when you procrastinate, you actually, we think, well, I'm going to do something now and I'll put that off to tomorrow.

03:15.142 --> 03:23.794
But the cost of procrastination is the life you could have lived to get that unpleasant task out of the way to get that

03:24.066 --> 03:30.372
thing that brings you sort of upheaval in your soul, that brings peace when you don't procrastinate.

03:30.852 --> 03:33.034
It's always there in the back of your mind.

03:33.075 --> 03:35.657
It's always there if you procrastinate.

03:35.717 --> 03:39.501
But if you settle it, it brings peace to your soul.

03:40.401 --> 03:53.714
Well, Jesus told two parables at the end of Matthew chapter 24 and the beginning of chapter 25 that we're going to talk about today that have to deal with the reality that it's later

03:53.922 --> 03:54.743
than you think.

03:56.825 --> 04:00.590
And the time for putting off is gone.

04:01.851 --> 04:03.934
The time to be prepared is here.

04:04.975 --> 04:10.141
You see, in Matthew chapter 24, Jesus tells us that He's going to come back.

04:10.842 --> 04:18.271
And He gives us some of the signs that will take place as we come toward the end of the age.

04:18.451 --> 04:20.754
And we went through all of that.

04:23.042 --> 04:25.425
This week has been a hard week.

04:26.546 --> 04:37.838
And I have been asked, and so it probably deserves to be answered, about how do I think this fits in to this whole dynamic of the second coming?

04:37.978 --> 04:44.104
And I would remind you, first of all, that there have been political assassinations in our past.

04:45.626 --> 04:49.490
Back to President Lincoln at the end of the Civil War.

04:49.826 --> 04:56.697
in the 1960s, the Kennedys, and Martin Luther King Jr., and there have been these sort of things in our past.

04:57.959 --> 05:15.666
But I would also say to you this, that at or near the end, there will be, according to Scripture, an increase in demonic hostility, especially toward those who believe.

05:17.602 --> 05:31.121
and I would also caution you and remind you that we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against spiritual forces of wickedness in high places.

05:33.023 --> 05:46.482
Our responsibility is to speak the truth in love, and that's hard sometimes, but it's still our responsibility, and it is our responsibility

05:46.722 --> 05:55.915
to share the only hope that the world has, and the only hope that the world has is the gospel of Jesus Christ.

05:56.756 --> 05:57.136
That's it.

05:58.899 --> 06:00.441
That is the hope of the world.

06:01.562 --> 06:04.326
And so Jesus tells us that He's going to return.

06:04.346 --> 06:15.762
And for those of you who might question that or doubt that, I would say to you that the return of Jesus is mentioned 318 times

06:16.034 --> 06:18.718
in the 260 chapters of the New Testament.

06:19.018 --> 06:24.607
There are 260 chapters in the New Testament in this part of the Bible, right here.

06:24.627 --> 06:28.853
And the return of Christ is mentioned 318 times.

06:29.915 --> 06:34.261
Now, frequency should tell us something about importance.

06:35.723 --> 06:45.778
Jesus himself in the four gospels mentions his return 21 times, and his point is always, be ready.

06:46.594 --> 06:49.197
And that's the point of these two parables.

06:49.257 --> 06:53.541
As a matter of fact, I could preach this sermon in two words.

06:54.663 --> 06:55.163
Be ready.

06:55.503 --> 06:55.904
That's it.

06:56.685 --> 06:58.367
Don't procrastinate.

06:58.387 --> 07:02.391
So let's look at these two parables and then I have several things to say about them.

07:03.012 --> 07:07.897
First of all, let's look at the parable, which is called the parable of the two slaves.

07:09.078 --> 07:12.882
Who then is the faithful and sensible slave?

07:13.282 --> 07:18.889
whom his master put in charge of his household slaves to give them their food at the proper time.

07:19.930 --> 07:26.958
Blessed is that slave, whom his master finds so doing when he comes."

07:27.899 --> 07:38.431
In other words, this servant is given a responsibility, a stewardship, and when the master comes back, he finds him doing exactly what he told him to do.

07:40.193 --> 07:40.754
Truly,

07:41.314 --> 07:44.100
I say to you, he will put him in charge of all his possessions.

07:45.182 --> 07:59.634
Verse 48, but if that evil slave says in his heart, my master is not coming for a long time and he begins to beat his fellow slaves and he eats and drinks for those who

07:59.842 --> 08:16.353
those habitually drunk, then the master of that slave will come on a day that he does not expect, and at an hour that he does not know, and he will cut him into and assign him a place with the hypocrites in that place, there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

08:18.077 --> 08:23.026
So the second slave, the one referred to as the evil slave, says, you know what?

08:23.298 --> 08:25.962
My master's gone and he put me in charge.

08:26.062 --> 08:27.405
And so I'm going to live it up.

08:27.505 --> 08:32.994
I'm going to live like I'm the master and I'm going to get, I'm going to live for pleasure.

08:33.194 --> 08:37.441
I'm going to live for, for hedonism.

08:37.481 --> 08:42.729
I'm just going to, I'm going to live it up on the backs of these other slaves.

08:43.651 --> 08:48.338
And Jesus said, but that servant's master will come.

08:48.962 --> 08:54.230
at a time or on a day when he does not expect at an hour when he does not know.

08:56.033 --> 08:56.774
So be prepared.

08:57.715 --> 08:58.757
There's a second parable.

08:59.358 --> 09:02.963
The second parable is called the parable of the 10 virgins.

09:02.983 --> 09:11.396
And the parable of the 10 virgins, maybe in modern parlance, the best metaphor is the parable of the 10 bridesmaids.

09:12.377 --> 09:13.479
It's a big wedding.

09:14.640 --> 09:17.825
It's going to be very expensive for the father of the bride.

09:17.845 --> 09:18.386
Actually,

09:18.754 --> 09:20.797
not so much in the ancient Near East.

09:22.059 --> 09:29.712
In biblical, in the biblical culture of the Bible in the first century, actually weddings were a little different than they are today.

09:29.772 --> 09:40.931
And in the interest of helping some of you to understand that it's not like weddings today, let me give a review that for some of you will be very much a review, I understand that.

09:41.071 --> 09:43.835
But here's the way weddings went.

09:43.855 --> 09:45.458
Parents would get together.

09:46.370 --> 09:50.576
and typically arrange for the marriage of a son and a daughter.

09:51.878 --> 09:56.646
And they would come together and make commitments and vows to one another.

09:56.686 --> 09:59.851
And that was called a betrovel.

10:00.632 --> 10:03.756
It was more than an engagement.

10:04.458 --> 10:06.841
It was less than a marriage ceremony.

10:07.682 --> 10:08.363
Let me explain.

10:09.265 --> 10:13.111
Commitments were made, pledges were made, vows were made.

10:14.533 --> 10:15.314
And so,

10:15.522 --> 10:22.352
In the eyes of the community, the young bride and groom were married.

10:22.412 --> 10:23.754
They were off the market.

10:23.834 --> 10:26.317
They were not available to anyone else.

10:27.759 --> 10:40.978
And so the bride groom would then go back to his father's house and the bride would remain with her parents for one year, for a year.

10:41.939 --> 10:43.922
By the way, during that period of time,

10:44.834 --> 10:52.602
The groom was typically adding a room onto his father's house where he and his bride would live.

10:52.702 --> 10:58.348
And that year he was adding a room in my father's house are many rooms.

10:59.349 --> 11:00.850
I go to prepare a place for you.

11:02.112 --> 11:02.512
Oh, wow.

11:02.792 --> 11:04.314
That kind of makes more sense now, doesn't it?

11:05.976 --> 11:12.082
But after a year, the bride groom, the groom would bring his friends

11:12.674 --> 11:33.426
and they would come to the house of the father of the bride and he would take the bride with him back to his family's house along with the procession of her friends and they would enter and they would have what was referred to as a wedding feast

11:33.602 --> 11:40.048
which wasn't a simple reception with the cake and the punch and the little green mints.

11:40.068 --> 11:43.832
It was actually a week long party.

11:45.053 --> 11:47.816
And so then that was the marriage.

11:48.136 --> 11:49.958
It was a great feast.

11:51.019 --> 11:56.003
Well, in this parable, there are these 10 bridesmaids.

11:56.043 --> 11:57.044
They are waiting.

11:57.064 --> 12:03.090
The day is coming when the bridegroom is supposed to come and get the bride and take her.

12:03.970 --> 12:06.274
But listen to this parable.

12:06.294 --> 12:12.644
Then the kingdom of heaven will be comparable to 10 virgins who took their lamps and went out to meet the groom.

12:13.826 --> 12:15.168
Five of them were foolish.

12:16.090 --> 12:16.991
Five were prudent.

12:17.892 --> 12:27.868
For when the foolish took their lamps, they did not take extra oil with them, but the prudent ones took oil in flask with their lamps.

12:28.790 --> 12:31.314
Now, while the groom was delaying,

12:32.034 --> 12:38.241
They all became drowsy and began to sleep, but at midnight, there finally was a shout.

12:38.862 --> 12:41.625
Behold the groom, come out to meet him."

12:42.466 --> 12:53.278
Then all those virgins got up and trimmed their lamps, but the foolish virgins said to the prudent ones, give us some of your oil because our lamps are going out.

12:53.979 --> 12:57.042
However, the prudent ones answered, no.

12:57.666 --> 13:04.813
Their most certainly would not be enough for us, and you too, go instead to the merchants and buy some for yourself.

13:05.734 --> 13:09.998
But while they were on their way to buy the oil, the groom came.

13:10.018 --> 13:18.686
And those who were ready went in with him to the wedding feast, and the door was shut.

13:18.706 --> 13:24.812
Yet later the other virgins also came saying, Lord, Lord, open up for us.

13:25.573 --> 13:26.514
But he answered,

13:27.138 --> 13:36.951
Truly I say to you, I do not know you beyond the alert then because you do not know the day or the hour.

13:37.973 --> 13:46.244
Now these two parables are meant to give us a singular message and that is be prepared.

13:47.365 --> 13:51.311
So let me make several statements that apply to both of these parables.

13:52.292 --> 13:56.818
Number one, be faithful today.

13:57.634 --> 13:59.537
not someday.

13:59.597 --> 14:10.872
In the parable of the two servants, one wants to be faithful, and so with daily faithfulness, he is obedient to his master.

14:11.272 --> 14:21.486
He does not know when the master will come back and call him to account, and so he prepares for the masters coming with daily faithfulness.

14:23.048 --> 14:24.210
The other servant

14:24.834 --> 14:35.967
decides to be lazy, to procrastinate, to put off obedience, saying that he is his master won't be coming for a long time anyway.

14:36.708 --> 14:44.738
He chooses someday, but the Lord calls us to be faithful today, each and every day.

14:45.379 --> 14:51.346
In the parable of the bridesmaids, there was that saved the date that went out.

14:51.650 --> 14:54.535
that they were supposed to be ready a year from the betrovel.

14:54.936 --> 14:56.999
Surely the groom was going to come.

14:57.881 --> 15:06.355
And yet when he came, there were some of these bridesmaids, these virgins who had prepared for his coming.

15:06.395 --> 15:12.445
They had extra oil in their lamps and in their flask in order to keep the fire burning into the night.

15:13.347 --> 15:17.554
And there were those who simply were not prepared.

15:18.274 --> 15:20.377
Well, there is something a bit unusual about this parable.

15:20.397 --> 15:28.448
There are a couple of things unusual about this parable, but Jesus was known for sort of throwing a curve ball when he would teach.

15:28.508 --> 15:32.894
And when you thought you knew the answer, Jesus would do something a little bit different.

15:33.234 --> 15:41.746
First of all, it would be highly, highly unusual for the groom to come in the middle of the night.

15:42.387 --> 15:44.690
That's not typically the way this worked.

15:45.858 --> 15:54.550
And when Jesus tells the story, there is something about it in verse four that I think is really, verse five rather is really interesting.

15:54.871 --> 16:10.012
He says, now while the groom was delaying, he was probably supposed to come in the daylight hours, but something happened that caused him to be delayed in Jesus' story.

16:10.773 --> 16:14.418
Not that Jesus is delayed somehow in coming back,

16:14.754 --> 16:21.240
But in the story that Jesus is telling, this bridegroom doesn't show up when they all expect him to show up.

16:22.001 --> 16:27.346
He comes at an unexpected time, a time that none of them anticipated.

16:27.807 --> 16:38.297
And that again goes to the point that Jesus has been making through all of this teaching that we need to be prepared because he is coming at a time when we don't expect him.

16:38.878 --> 16:39.959
So be prepared.

16:41.080 --> 16:43.442
The second thing that's unusual about this parable,

16:44.226 --> 16:56.859
is at the end of the parable, when the foolish bridesmaids or virgins go and try to find some oil and they come back, the door is already shut.

16:57.379 --> 17:12.434
And when they knock on the door, asking to be let in, since these are sort of friends of the bride and the groomsmen were friends of the groom, you would think that they would be allowed in.

17:12.930 --> 17:21.142
But Jesus throws another curveball in at that time and he says to them, truly, I say to you, I don't know you.

17:22.344 --> 17:24.327
What an interesting line.

17:24.347 --> 17:35.584
And that one, by the way, has confused scholars for generations when people have looked at this, when you really look deeply at the culture of weddings at that time.

17:36.366 --> 17:39.250
But Jesus is moving at this moment

17:39.938 --> 17:47.547
from His temporal teaching, from the earthly teaching of the parable to the eternal meaning of the parable.

17:48.568 --> 17:57.960
And the eternal meaning of the parable is that those who know Him, those who have a relationship with Him will be invited into His wedding feast.

17:57.980 --> 18:01.624
That's why I told you that story, at custom of weddings.

18:02.686 --> 18:09.714
And those who are not prepared for them, those who've not trusted Him, those who've not received Him as Savior and Lord,

18:10.114 --> 18:15.500
will be turned away and he will say to them, I do not know you."

18:17.241 --> 18:22.927
So Jesus says to us, be prepared today, not just someday.

18:24.389 --> 18:29.314
Five had oil, the five foolish virgins had the oil that ran out.

18:30.936 --> 18:36.882
A few months ago, my wife and I were gonna grill on our gas grill.

18:37.826 --> 18:39.729
And she said, would you go out and start the grill?

18:39.749 --> 18:44.395
And so I go out and I start the grill and I get it good and hot and I scrub it down really good.

18:44.435 --> 18:50.303
And, you know, from the residue of the last stuff we grilled and whatever it was, we were grilling that night.

18:50.363 --> 18:51.104
I think it was chicken.

18:51.785 --> 18:55.170
I take it out and I throw it on there and I noticed the temperature is good and hot.

18:55.971 --> 19:04.563
And I went back and a few, you know, set a timer on my phone and I went back in a few minutes and I noticed that the temperature was decreasing.

19:06.325 --> 19:07.026
And I thought, oh.

19:07.298 --> 19:07.959
This is not good.

19:09.982 --> 19:18.153
And I went around to my gas grill and I looked down at the gas tank and it's got a little gauge, which is kind of ingenious.

19:18.213 --> 19:27.886
It's a weight gauge and it was showing me that my gas, my propane container was empty and I'm not halfway finished with cooking this chicken yet.

19:28.667 --> 19:34.194
So I turned and went to my spare and the first thing I noticed

19:34.370 --> 19:39.556
when I looked at the spare was that little blue cap was not on the top of it.

19:40.837 --> 19:47.304
Oh no, not only am I out of propane here, but I had forgotten to go take my spare and trade it in.

19:47.744 --> 19:49.907
I am out of propane.

19:50.007 --> 19:50.868
I am out of gas.

19:50.928 --> 19:52.209
And so what did I do?

19:54.592 --> 19:56.094
We cooked the chicken on the stove.

19:56.194 --> 19:56.995
That's what we did.

19:57.035 --> 19:59.197
There wasn't any time to do that.

19:59.237 --> 20:00.358
I don't know how that's going to work.

20:00.398 --> 20:03.922
If I wait 15, 20 minutes to go to the store and get some more propane,

20:04.482 --> 20:06.185
And so we cooked the chicken on the stove.

20:07.126 --> 20:08.468
I was out of oil.

20:08.568 --> 20:14.457
I was out of propane in the same way that these virgins were out of oil.

20:15.238 --> 20:16.039
Be prepared.

20:16.119 --> 20:18.022
When you're prepared, there's no panic.

20:18.663 --> 20:19.664
Don't wait for tomorrow.

20:20.265 --> 20:21.547
Don't wait for another day.

20:21.627 --> 20:23.790
Don't wait until you think it's time.

20:23.871 --> 20:29.939
The Bible says in John chapter 9 verse 4, we must work the works of Him who sent me as long as it is day.

20:30.400 --> 20:32.744
Night is coming when no one can work.

20:33.124 --> 20:34.386
There's coming a day.

20:34.786 --> 20:36.008
when it will be too late.

20:36.789 --> 20:38.331
Be faithful today, not someday.

20:39.173 --> 20:46.684
Second, you cannot borrow spiritual readiness.

20:47.365 --> 20:50.530
You cannot borrow spiritual readiness.

20:51.131 --> 21:01.046
The unfaithful servant in the first parable Jesus told lived with a false sense of security that someday would never come.

21:02.388 --> 21:04.050
And somehow he would escape

21:04.322 --> 21:10.473
the wrath of the Master, that He wouldn't have to experience the consequences of His actions.

21:11.135 --> 21:20.332
The foolish virgins very specifically ask the other virgins to give them some of their oil, because their lamps were going out.

21:21.113 --> 21:25.842
But in verse 9, the prudent ones answered, no.

21:26.146 --> 21:31.954
No, there most certainly would not be enough for us and for you to go to the merchants and buy some for yourself.

21:32.375 --> 21:43.790
Now, when some people look at that, they say, well, how selfish, how selfish of those that had brought extra that they wouldn't share, shouldn't they have just shared that?

21:45.172 --> 21:48.157
Jesus is making a point here that is incredibly important.

21:48.217 --> 21:55.026
And that is that spiritual readiness cannot be borrowed.

21:55.778 --> 22:09.257
That oil is the symbol of spiritual preparation, of giving your life to Christ, of turning to Him in repentance and faith, and each person is responsible for themselves.

22:10.258 --> 22:14.984
Your grandparents' readiness will not transfer to you.

22:15.225 --> 22:18.469
Your parents' readiness will not transfer to you.

22:18.950 --> 22:24.818
In Romans 14, verse 12, Paul writes, so then each one of us

22:25.186 --> 22:28.712
will give an account of himself to God.

22:29.533 --> 22:36.645
You are not going to be responsible for Bob McCartney, and Bob McCartney is not going to stand there and be responsible for anyone else before Jesus.

22:37.566 --> 22:41.272
Your spiritual readiness is upon you.

22:41.452 --> 22:45.599
Salvation cannot be borrowed.

22:45.639 --> 22:47.462
It cannot.

22:48.904 --> 22:52.370
It cannot be passed down like a spiritual heirloom.

22:53.026 --> 23:03.240
Now I want to say to this to you that we ought to raise our children in a way in which we pass on our Christian heritage, but we try to pass it on.

23:03.321 --> 23:05.644
They must receive it for themselves.

23:07.767 --> 23:14.697
And so we are called on to know that spiritual readiness cannot be borrowed.

23:15.918 --> 23:18.021
Every now and then I sign up for races.

23:18.101 --> 23:19.223
I'm still trying to do that.

23:20.765 --> 23:21.426
You can grow.

23:21.602 --> 23:23.344
old, but you don't have to grow up.

23:23.724 --> 23:27.668
And so I haven't convinced myself that I need to stop this yet.

23:28.228 --> 23:31.251
My physician says I need to, and I'm not listening to him.

23:32.012 --> 23:36.637
And I love him, but I'm not.

23:37.497 --> 23:39.399
But I sign up for these races.

23:39.459 --> 23:39.920
And you know what?

23:40.260 --> 23:43.583
At the end of the form where you sign up, they always say this.

23:45.225 --> 23:48.188
No refunds, no transfers.

23:48.248 --> 23:50.450
In other words, if you don't do it, you lose it.

23:50.594 --> 23:52.416
You can't give it to somebody else.

23:53.998 --> 23:57.923
And spiritual preparation is exactly the same.

23:57.963 --> 23:59.104
There are no transfers.

24:00.265 --> 24:01.587
You can't give it to somebody else.

24:01.607 --> 24:05.852
And by the way, you can't share a little grace with someone else.

24:05.892 --> 24:08.735
You must experience the grace of God for yourself.

24:09.816 --> 24:15.163
Finally, when the door closes, it will close suddenly and swiftly.

24:16.344 --> 24:18.066
For the slaves in verse 50,

24:19.554 --> 24:24.400
The master of that slave will come on a day when he does not expect in an hour when he does not know.

24:25.421 --> 24:33.410
For the virgins, when the door was shut and the wedding feast began, it was never opened again.

24:34.731 --> 24:37.535
Someday the door of grace will be closed.

24:38.676 --> 24:41.559
Salvation is available today.

24:41.579 --> 24:47.346
Dr. Robert Jeffress, who stood in this very place and preached for many years,

24:47.874 --> 24:56.367
and was my immediate predecessor, wrote in his book, Perfect Ending, the suddenness of the master's arrival is the point.

24:57.128 --> 25:05.681
Christ will return when least expected, and opportunities for repentance will be gone.

25:06.963 --> 25:12.532
Grace is available now, but it will not be available forever.

25:13.774 --> 25:16.658
There will be a day when Jesus

25:17.282 --> 25:25.053
will say the time is up and the door of grace will close.

25:26.996 --> 25:27.837
What should we do?

25:29.159 --> 25:38.313
Well, let me give you five practical things that I believe we should do in light of being ready for the return of the Lord.

25:39.755 --> 25:44.882
First of all, we need to see the spiritual battle around us.

25:45.954 --> 25:49.119
We are engaged in a spiritual battle.

25:50.201 --> 25:59.396
The Bible tells us that we do not wrestle with flesh and blood, but with spiritual forces of wickedness in high places.

26:00.438 --> 26:04.325
There is a spiritual battle going on all around us.

26:05.366 --> 26:12.338
And as followers of Jesus, we need to understand that much of the cultural chaos

26:13.186 --> 26:15.649
is not so much a cultural issue.

26:15.769 --> 26:23.459
It is a spiritual issue that the gospel of Jesus Christ is desperately needed in our country and in our culture.

26:24.580 --> 26:33.872
We need to understand this is a spiritual battle that is raging and our weapons are not carnal.

26:35.414 --> 26:37.737
The sword of the spirit is the word of God.

26:37.777 --> 26:38.738
It's truth.

26:40.162 --> 26:42.124
is made mighty through prayer.

26:42.224 --> 26:43.345
That's what the Bible says.

26:44.567 --> 26:48.211
And so we need to understand there is a spiritual battle raging around us.

26:49.052 --> 26:54.758
As we approach the end, we need to fight for the souls of our children.

26:56.840 --> 27:00.264
We need to fight for the souls of our children.

27:01.425 --> 27:07.612
We need to instill in them that they were created on purpose with a purpose.

27:08.253 --> 27:09.554
They are not some

27:09.666 --> 27:12.991
random collection of cells.

27:13.752 --> 27:16.817
They are not advanced algae or educated apes.

27:16.857 --> 27:19.161
They were created in the image of God.

27:19.501 --> 27:25.570
We need to instill the biblical worldview that God created, boys and God created, girls.

27:27.654 --> 27:28.635
And that's a good thing.

27:30.658 --> 27:35.906
We need to talk about the reality that God created a perfect world.

27:35.926 --> 27:38.450
Then He put the people in it, people just like us.

27:39.874 --> 27:41.336
who sinned and messed it up.

27:41.916 --> 27:47.483
And because of that, we need a Savior because we cannot save ourselves.

27:48.323 --> 27:51.948
We need to fight for the souls of the next generation.

27:52.808 --> 27:54.791
For some of you, that's your grandchildren.

27:55.652 --> 27:56.653
Maybe not your children.

27:57.634 --> 28:00.757
But we need to understand that their souls are on the line.

28:02.119 --> 28:08.466
Third, when we look at the coming of Christ, we need to invest in kingdom causes.

28:10.402 --> 28:18.693
We spend so much time investing in what ultimately is going to be wood, hay, and straw.

28:18.713 --> 28:19.814
It's so temporary.

28:20.054 --> 28:28.465
We spend more of our time and our resources on things that will not matter rather than gold and silver and precious stones.

28:29.767 --> 28:31.830
I've only been to Italy once in my life.

28:32.671 --> 28:38.418
But you know, if you go to Italy, they can show you things that were built 2,000 years ago.

28:40.386 --> 28:43.169
I mean, we think something's old if it's 20 years old.

28:44.850 --> 28:49.034
We think something's old if it's 50, it's an antique if it's 50 years old.

28:49.095 --> 28:50.256
I think that's the rule, isn't it?

28:51.717 --> 28:59.064
But you go to Italy and there are things that are 2,000 years old, 1,000 years old, 500 years old.

28:59.605 --> 29:00.626
Do you know why they're there?

29:00.666 --> 29:03.589
Because they weren't built with wood, hay, and straw.

29:03.629 --> 29:04.910
They were built with marble.

29:07.312 --> 29:09.074
Invest your life.

29:10.306 --> 29:15.072
and things that are going to matter, and everything of this world is going to perish, everything.

29:15.813 --> 29:28.990
But when you invest in kingdom causes through your church, when you give resources to advance the gospel, what you are doing is building with gold and silver and precious stone.

29:29.030 --> 29:37.201
You're building with marble, and it's going to last.

29:37.221 --> 29:38.002
Jesus said,

29:38.818 --> 29:50.961
Don't spend your time and your resources on the things of this world that are going to perish, but build, but seek to invest in things and give to things that are going to last for all eternity.

29:52.403 --> 29:56.030
Number four, bring people to church.

29:57.192 --> 29:58.094
Bring people to church.

29:59.757 --> 30:02.322
I would say share the gospel, yes, do that.

30:03.010 --> 30:06.255
And we've got some moments coming up this fall where we're going to train you to do that.

30:06.295 --> 30:07.798
Some of you say, I don't feel comfortable doing that.

30:07.818 --> 30:13.166
Well, then at least bring them to church where somebody else can share the gospel with them.

30:13.186 --> 30:16.452
Somebody who does feel comfortable doing it.

30:16.472 --> 30:21.680
Bring people to church and finally wake up your spirit.

30:21.700 --> 30:22.982
Wake up your spirit.

30:24.405 --> 30:30.194
It seems to me that many of us in the church are spiritually sleepwalking.

30:31.586 --> 30:36.314
And we need to wake up and be ready for the coming of the Lord.

30:38.637 --> 30:46.710
But finally, if you have never trusted Jesus as your Savior, you can't wait till someday.

30:47.952 --> 30:49.895
It has to be today.

30:51.638 --> 30:54.162
Readiness is an urgent matter.

30:54.786 --> 31:00.852
In 2 Corinthians 6 to the Apostle Paul says, at the acceptable time, I listen to you.

31:01.132 --> 31:07.139
And on the day of salvation, I helped you behold now is the acceptable time.

31:07.419 --> 31:10.582
Behold, now is the day of salvation.

31:13.145 --> 31:15.667
If you have never trusted Christ, I plead with you.

31:18.490 --> 31:19.551
I plead with you.

31:20.792 --> 31:22.354
Repent of your sin.

31:23.522 --> 31:31.053
totally trust that what Jesus did on the cross is the full payment for your sin.

31:33.035 --> 31:35.239
That He died to take away your sin.

31:35.279 --> 31:51.922
He died as your substitute to take a death that you deserve, to pay a price for a debt that you had occurred and believe

31:53.730 --> 32:02.983
that he was vindicated for our justification by his resurrection, that he literally and physically was raised from the dead, and he is alive today.

32:03.344 --> 32:07.389
That is the Christ that I call upon you to put your faith in.

32:09.713 --> 32:21.970
The risen reigning king of the universe, and his name is Jesus, who loves you so much that he would die for you.

32:23.874 --> 32:27.745
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, which is not false.

32:27.765 --> 32:36.770
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes, or go to fbcwf.org.

32:36.791 --> 32:38.034
We'll see you next week.

